\section{Formal Development}

Correctness theorem that we will aim at:

If:

\begin{itemize}
\item $[[G |- sc ~> c | G']]$
\item $[[G ~ srho]]$
\item $[[G |- srho ~> rho; crho1, crho2]]$
\end{itemize}

Then:

\begin{itemize}
\item $[[srho |- sc !! srho'; sobs]]$
\item $[[rho |- c !! rho' ; ckt]]$
\item $[[crho1, crho2 |- ckt !! crho1', crho2'; sobs]]$
\end{itemize}

